    "summary": "Goal oriented principal consultant and project manager with more than 25 years experience in the field of large and small scale energy systems (a.o. techno-economical feasibility studies, performance testing, process improvement), and in addition more than 10 years in process automation and process simulation of energy conversion systems.\nCatchwords: power plant performance, feasibility and energy policy studies, energy-supply studies for large consumers (\u2018multi-utility approach\u2019), scheduling of multiple means of energy production, sustainable energy, co- and tri-generation, waste-heat-to-power, heat pumps, steam and gas turbines, gas engines, boilers, CO2-capture, energy cycle calculations (steady state and dynamic), process automation, measurement and control, advanced process control, dynamic modelling and process simulation, operator training simulators, signal processing, DCS-, PLC- and SCADA-systems, condition monitoring, operations support systems (mainly in the field of large scale power generation, heat distribution, greenhouse horticulture, built environment, energy intensive industry and hospitals).\n\nSpecialties: - Analyzing complex energy systems by sufficiently detailed models (steady state and/or dynamic), providing in depth process information for solving the complex questions with respect to a.o. power production, (hourly, daily or yearly) energy demand in industry, built environment and greenhouse horticulture and the (energetically or economically) optimal supply of this demand.\n- feasibility studies\n- application fields: thermal and concentrated solar power plants, integrated coal gasification combined cycle (ICGCC), air separation, biomass, heat/cold storage systems, greenhouse energy systems",
